1️⃣ CASE (If-Else in SQL)
Simple Idea

CASE is used to apply conditions (like if-else in programming)

👉 It answers:
“If condition is true → do this, else do that”

Mental Model 🧠
CASE = SQL version of if-else
Example Table
name	marks
Akshay	85
Rahul	72
Neha	90
Problem

👉 “Classify students as Pass/Fail”

SQL Query
SELECT name,
CASE
    WHEN marks >= 75 THEN 'Pass'
    ELSE 'Fail'
END AS result
FROM students;
Output
name	result
Akshay	Pass
Rahul	Fail
Neha	Pass
Multiple Conditions
SELECT name,
CASE
    WHEN marks >= 90 THEN 'Excellent'
    WHEN marks >= 75 THEN 'Good'
    ELSE 'Average'
END AS grade
FROM students;
Python Connection 🧠
if marks >= 90:
    grade = "Excellent"
elif marks >= 75:
    grade = "Good"
else:
    grade = "Average"

👉 CASE = same logic inside SQL

Why CASE is Powerful

✔ Used in reports
✔ Used in dashboards
✔ Used in interview queries

Memory Trick 🧠
CASE = If-Else in SQL
2️⃣ NULL Handling (Missing Data)
Simple Idea

NULL means “no value” (missing data)

👉 It is NOT:

0 ❌
empty string ❌

👉 It means: unknown / not available

Example Table
name	marks
Akshay	85
Rahul	NULL
Neha	90
Problem

👉 Find students with missing marks

SQL Query
SELECT * FROM students
WHERE marks IS NULL;
Opposite
SELECT * FROM students
WHERE marks IS NOT NULL;
Important Rule ⚠️

❌ Wrong:

marks = NULL

✔ Correct:

marks IS NULL
Python Connection 🧠
if s["marks"] is None:
Why NULL Handling is Important

✔ Missing data is common
✔ Prevents wrong calculations
✔ Required in real-world datasets

Combining CASE + NULL 🔥
SELECT name,
CASE
    WHEN marks IS NULL THEN 'No Data'
    WHEN marks >= 75 THEN 'Pass'
    ELSE 'Fail'
END AS result
FROM students;
Memory Trick 🧠
NULL = Missing value
IS NULL → check missing
🔥 Placement Insight

Very common questions:

Q1: What is NULL?

👉 Missing / unknown value

Q2: Difference between NULL and 0?
NULL	0
No value	Actual value
Unknown	Known
Q3: Why can't we use = NULL?

👉 Because NULL is not a value → it’s unknown

Quick Revision (1 Minute)
CASE → if-else logic

NULL → missing value
IS NULL → check missing
IS NOT NULL → check present
